<br>
Every so often, a member of this group -- a cult, or an organization -- catches up with her and assigns her something: to deliver a message, to follow someone, to obtain an item. <br>
<br>
She'd be either a bard or rogue, half-elven or wood elven (but not a tree hugger -- more like a bottom-feeder). And she would resent the hell out of this group, who has something to hold over her head -- an old crime, an old debt, or maybe just the threat of death itself. And she'd be constantly on the move, trying to avoid their next assignment... but of course they always find her. <br>
<br>
Perusing these wonderful boards I saw an idea for a cult of the dragon, and there seem to be some dedicated roleplayers here... just wondering if this is the sort of story line anyone would get a kick out of participating in... <br>
<br>
Echo (for the moment -- name subject to change upon approval by Verant.)<br>
<br>
